We first calculate the Gross Profit Margin using the formula:

  Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100

Using the income statement values:  
  Gross Profit = 287062.51  
  Total Revenue = 791992.51  

Thus,  
  Gross Profit Margin = (287062.51 / 791992.51) × 100 ≈ 36.25%

Next, we calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio using the common formula:

  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities

From the balance sheet and cash flow statement:  
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -4504752.68  
  Total Current Liabilities (from the balance sheet) = 3389719.66  

Thus,  
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -4504752.68 / 3389719.66 ≈ -1.33
